# Padroes Svelte 5 para Componentes

## Estrutura Base

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  interface Props {
    variant?: "default" | "outline" | "ghost";
    size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
    disabled?: boolean;
    onclick?: (event: MouseEvent) => void;
  }

  let {
    variant = "default",
    size = "md",
    disabled = false,
    onclick,
    children,
  }: Props = $props();

  let hovered = $state(false);
</script>

<button
  class="btn btn--{variant} btn--{size}"
  {disabled}
  {onclick}
  onmouseenter={() => (hovered = true)}
  onmouseleave={() => (hovered = false)}
>
  {@render children?.()}
</button>
```

## Runes ($props, $state, $derived, $effect)

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  // Props (substitui export let)
  let { count = 0, label }: { count?: number; label: string } = $props();

  // Estado reativo
  let internalCount = $state(count);

  // Valor derivado (substitui $:)
  let doubled = $derived(internalCount * 2);

  // Efeito colateral
  $effect(() => {
    console.log(`Count mudou para: ${internalCount}`);
    return () => console.log("cleanup");
  });
</script>
```

## Snippets (substitui slots)

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import type { Snippet } from "svelte";

  interface Props {
    header?: Snippet;
    children: Snippet;
    footer?: Snippet<[{ count: number }]>;
  }

  let { header, children, footer }: Props = $props();
</script>

<div class="card">
  {#if header}
    <header>{@render header()}</header>
  {/if}
  {@render children()}
  {#if footer}
    <footer>{@render footer({ count: 42 })}</footer>
  {/if}
</div>
```

## Bindings e Blocos de Controle

```svelte
<input bind:value={name} />

{#if loading}
  <Spinner />
{:else if error}
  <ErrorMessage message={error} />
{:else}
  {#each items as item (item.id)}
    <Item {item} />
  {/each}
{/if}
```

## Convencoes

- Usar runes do Svelte 5 (`$props`, `$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`)
- Snippets em vez de slots para composicao
- Props tipadas com interface TypeScript
- Callbacks via props (ex: `onclick`) em vez de `createEventDispatcher`
- Cleanup em `$effect` retornando funcao
- Sempre usar key em `{#each}` com `(item.id)`
